cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on developing a handover mechanism for a cellular-connected drone system, which involves wireless communication and mobility support. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning algorithms for optimizing handover decisions suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on mobility support and control of drone operations suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
